title: South Umpqua baseball pounds Marshfield in Far West contest
title_page: South Umpqua baseball pounds Marshfield in Far West contest
maintext:
COOS BAY — The South Umpqua Lancers picked up a 15-6 win on the road against Marshfield on Tuesday in a Far West League baseball game.
“We jumped out to a 9-2 lead, but let them back in a little in the fourth inning to make it a three run game,” said S.U. coach Steve Stebbins. “We scored six runs in the top of the seventh to make the close ball game not so close anymore.”
Cody Gray batted 4-for-6 with two doubles and an RBI for the Lancers (2-10, 1-2 FW). Tucker Pence went 3-for-4 with an RBI and a double, Nikai Sinohui batted 2-for-4 with one RBI, Johnathan Warner was 2-for-4 and Taylor Gross went 2-for-5 with one RBI.
The Lancers play a makeup game with North Bend on Tuesday.
